md:
giải nghĩa từ "clubs" sang tiếng việt; đưa ra nghĩa tiếng việt theo từ loại và đưa ra câu ví dụ, các từ liên quan và các từ trái nghĩa.

* Clubs (noun) - Câu lạc bộ
	+ Meaning: A group of people who share a common interest or activity.
	+ Example sentence: "She joined a book club to meet new people who share her passion for reading."
	+ Related words: team, organization, society
	+ Antonyms: individual, solo

* Clubs (verb) - Đánh, đập
	+ Meaning: To hit or strike something with a club or a heavy object.
	+ Example sentence: "The police officer clubbed the suspect to subdue him."
	+ Related words: hit, strike, beat
	+ Antonyms: caress, pat, stroke

* Clubs (plural noun) - Đồ chơi, dụng cụ
	+ Meaning: A set of objects used for a particular activity or game.
	+ Example sentence: "He brought his golf clubs to the course to play a round of golf."
	+ Related words: equipment, gear, tools
	+ Antonyms: none

Note: The meanings and examples provided are just a few of the possible interpretations of the word "clubs". The word can have different meanings and connotations depending on the context in which it is used.
